>>when written to 
>>causes your module to properly clean everything up
>>and prevent anyone 
>>from getting new accesses.  This then allows you to
>>remove the module 
>>cleanly.  Note that it may not be possible to
>>cleanly deregister, 
>>depending on what your module is doing.
